s:67363:"<h1>Change log in version 500.2.1 (2025040806)</h1>

<ol>
<li>Fix "Information block row displays column mode" - #44.</li>
<li>Fix "Home Navigation Expand/Collapse".</li>
<li>Fix "Missing 'Bulk actions' on course page".</li>
<li>Fix "Persistent Warning after upgrade of theme" - #45.</li>
<li>Fix 'Missing icons in Administration block'.</li>
<li>Fix 'Cannot edit single section page section name at top of the page'.</li>
<li>Fix 'News ticker tickertext setting shown when newstickercount is 0'.</li>
<li>State Font Awesome icon for 'core:i/viewsection'.  Effectively ensuring it is the correct colour.</li>
<li>Fix 'Position of course index link when there is a badge attached to it'.</li>
<li>Fix 'Course index link when hover / focus'.</li>
<li>Tidy course expand / collapse and action menu icons.</li>
<li>Tidy 'Manage course categories and courses' page.</li>
<li>State Font Awesome icon for 'core:i/bulk_edit'.  Effectively ensuring it is the correct colour.</li>
<li>Tidy 'Tiles with overlay' 'frontpagerenderer' setting.</li>
<li>Refix 'Frontpage course boxes' styling as previous fix caused issues on 'course/index.php' page.</li>
<li>Fix 'Use a cog for the header context menu when using core Font Awesome to be consistent with the theme version of the font'.</li>
<li>Fix 'Missing theme reset callback as the 'navbardisplaymenuarrow' setting changes the SCSS'.</li>
<li>Fix 'Missing right margin on navbar zoom icons'.</li>
</ol>

<h1>Change log in version 500.2.0 (2025040805)</h1>

<h2>Important</h2>

<p>From feedback and consideration of such I have re-evaluated the organisation and understanding of what Adaptable provides in terms of functionality.  Going through the settings its clear that something needed to be done.  To bring order to the chaos as the theme has evolved over many years.  To bring understanding of what a setting does through its name and description.  To be the first point of understanding without maintaining secondary sources that so easily could become out of date and inaccurate.  To this end, this version brings a lot of changes.  From your perspective though, the upgrade should just work.  The names change but their values retained.  Importing JSON property settings that you've previously kept should still work as the code knows what has changed and will perform the transition for you, reporting on what its done.  The most significant change is the header, where I hope the words now express what each 'layout' (was 'style') is.</p>

<p>To be consistent across releases for major versions, I've introduced a 'Feature version' property that you might notice.  That's there to ensure that upgrades that have already happened do not happen again and for the JSON property settings to make a similar decision upon.</p>

<p>When I was updating my copy of the <a href="https://moodle.org/plugins/theme_boost_union">Boost Union</a> theme, I noticed that it provides additional information during the upgrade process.  To this end I have implemented my own solution that details what is happening during the process.  If you need to, then please make note of it as the information is not stored.  Credit to <a href="https://github.com/abias">Alexander Bias</a> for the idea.</p>

<p>I have done a lot of tiding of the styles, removing what I understand to be redundant in the process.  If I have removed a style that was there but now is not and you use it, then please raise and issue with a full description and screen shot(s) and I'll consider putting it back.</p>

<p>All of these changes come with risk, I'm only human and whilst I have striven to be accurate there is a chance that bugs have been introduced.  Therefore as always, testing on a test server is vital to confirm that you're happy before moving to production.  However no AI has been involved and hence the changes have been undertaken by decisions based upon experience, knowledge, and understanding of both software engineering and code.</p>

<h2>Changes</h2>

<ol>
<li>Remove 'fonttitlecolorcourse' as redundant.</li>
<li>Move header font settings to 'Header' settings tab.</li>
<li>Clarify heading font settings.</li>
<li>Removed 'topmenufontsize' setting as redundant.</li>
<li>Remove redundant 'langmenu' styles.</li>
<li>Move header 'style' colour settings to 'Header' settings tab and clarify the elements of the header.</li>
<li>Fix 'main header row' menu text colour.</li>
<li>Fix social icons on the 'main header row' colour.</li>
<li>Add 'feature_version' internal setting to keep track of features across major Moodle versions.</li>
<li>Upgrading and property import now reports on setting name updates.</li>
<li>Added 'autocomplete="off"' to admin settings forms to hopefully prevent revertion of changes after importing settings, as the browser remembers what you had and not what the imported setting changed the value to.  This can happen if you then make changes without logging out then logging back in again.  Refreshing the settings page or going back to it does not help.</li>
<li>Show version information when upgrading.</li>
<li>Removed deprecated setting 'enableheading', replaced by 'enablecoursetitle'.</li>
<li>Removed deprecated setting 'coursepageheaderhidesitetitle', replaced by 'coursepageheaderhidetitle'.</li>
<li>Removed deprecated setting 'enablezoomshowtext', replaced by 'navbardisplaytitles'.</li>
<li>Removed deprecated settings 'responsivecoursetitle' / 'responsivesitetitle', replaced by 'responsiveheadertitle'.</li>
<li>Removed deprecated setting 'jssection', replaced by 'customjs'.</li>
<li>Removed deprecated setting 'jssectionrestricted', replaced by 'customjsrestricted'.</li>
<li>Decided not to remove BCU front page info boxes.</li>
<li>Moved 'Marketing block colours' from 'Colours' to 'Marketing blocks'.  Note: It is still my intention to remove marketing blocks in favour of information blocks.</li>
<li>Removed deprecated 'marketimage' CSS class.</li>
<li>Moved 'favicon' and 'enablesavecanceloverlay' settings from 'Header' to 'General'.</li>
<li>Changed 'Header social' to 'Header search and social'.</li>
<li>Moved 'headersearchandsocial' and 'searchboxpadding' settings from 'Header' to 'Header search and social'.</li>
<li>Tidy the footer.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'pageheaderheight' to 'headermainrowminheight' and moved to the 'Header' settings tab.</li>
<li>Align the main header row content with the menu row.</li>
<li>Nearly all, bar responsive, breadcrumb settings on the 'Header' settings tab.</li>
<li>All messages and notifications settings on the 'Header' settings tab.</li>
<li>Footer colours on the 'Footer' settings tab.</li>
<li>Moved 'tilesbordercolor' setting to the 'Frontpage courses list' settings tab.</li>
<li>Coventry / Overlay colour settings on the 'Frontpage courses list' settings tab.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'dividingline' to 'headertoprowdividingline' and moved to the 'Header' settings tab.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'dividingline2' to 'footerdividingline' and moved to the 'Footer' settings tab.</li>
<li>Remove strings already in core.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'headerbkcolor' to 'headertoprowbkcolour' on the 'Header' settings tab.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'headertextcolor' to 'headertoprowtextcolour' on the 'Header' settings tab.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'headerbkcolor2' to 'headermainrowbkcolour' on the 'Header' settings tab.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'headertextcolor2' to 'headermainrowtextcolour' on the 'Header' settings tab.</li>
<li>Moved 'Activities' above 'Forum' on 'Colours' setting tab.</li>
<li>Removed 'blockplace1' CSS class.</li>
<li>Tidied up SCSS to remove some redundant styles and improve organisation.</li>
<li>Validate value of 'coursetitlemaxwidth' when set externally to the UI.</li>
<li>Fix section course section name and 'Collapse' / 'Expand' all text to follow the 'sectionheadingcolor' setting.</li>
<li>Tidy course section header.</li>
<li>Add new settings 'fontheaderlevelX' on the 'Fonts' settings tab, where X is 1 to 6 to set the size of the headings.</li>
<li>Tidy settings save / discard floating buttons.</li>
<li>Fix Font Awesome icons on the administration / navigation blocks.</li>
<li>Fix editing button on pages.</li>
<li>Improve 'fontsize' setting to allow pixel and rem value units.</li>
<li>Fix dynamic property warnings in 'adaptable_admin_setting_configtemplate.php'.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'responsiveheader' to use 'flex' based responsive values rather than 'block'.  This means that the
'main-header-row' will have its content centred vertically.</li>
<li>State that only header layout one responds to the 'responsiveheader' setting.</li>
<li>State the setting error on the 'Information' tab if one or more settings fail to save.</li>
<li>Fix 'Only output activity navigation markup if there is activity navigation to show'.</li>
<li>Improve FontAwesome icons and replace 'compass' with 'circle' for navigation items.</li>
<li>Fix 'Breadcrumb editing button icon too close to text'.</li>
<li>Fix 'Badge background is a different colour when the underlying background is not white'.</li>
<li>Add tools menu to 'mobileprimarynav' drawer.</li>
<li>Add user favourites menu to 'mobileprimarynav' drawer.</li>
<li>Fix 'Frontpage course boxes' styling.</li>
<li>Remove 'boxfooter' from course box as can find no reason for its existence.</li>
<li>Adjust position of course box button for 'Coventry tiles'.</li>
<li>Fix 'Group mode icons on modules'.</li>
<li>Fix core i/groupn.svg icon size.  Was 24 x 24, should be 20 x 16 in line with others.</li>
<li>Add tools menu icon setting for each tools menu.</li>
<li>Moved 'navbardisplayicons', 'navbardisplaytitles' and 'navbardisplaymenuarrow' settings from 'Navbar styles' to
'Navbar' settings tab.</li>
<li>Add user favourites menu icon setting for the user favourites menu.</li>
<li>Fix spacing on language menu when the language name is shown in the dropdown title.</li>
<li>Add 'secondarycolourtext' setting to set the text colour for elements that use the 'bg-secondary' Bootstrap CSS class, such as a badge.
Also added '--ad-secondary-text' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'maincolor' to 'maincolour' on the 'Colours' settings tab and added '--ad-main-colour' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'fontcolor' to 'fontcolour' on the 'Colours' settings tab and added '--ad-font-colour' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'regionmaincolor' to 'regionmaincolour' on the 'Colours' settings tab and added '--ad-regionmain-colour' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'regionmaintextcolor' to 'regionmaintextcolour' on the 'Colours' settings tab and added '--ad-regionmaintext-colour' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'linkcolor' to 'linkcolour' on the 'Colours' settings tab and added '--ad-link-colour' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Added '--ad-linkhover-colour' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'dimmedtextcolor' to 'dimmedtextcolour' on the 'Colours' settings tab and added '--ad-dimmedtext-colour' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Added '--ad-selectiontext-colour' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Added '--as-selectionbackground-colour' CSS variable to use.</li>
<li>Ensure that the lang menu is only shown when specified for the layout in the config.php file.</li>
<li>Tidy / improve search box in the navbar.</li>
<li>Add site shortname (if not empty) to JSON properties filename.</li>
<li>Changed setting 'coursepageblocksliderenabled' to 'coursepageblockinfoenabled' on the 'Courses' tab.</li>
<li>Fix activities icon not being a Font Awesome one when adding an activity on a course.</li>
<li>Improve 'This course' icons.</li>
<li>Reduce block list indentation.</li>
</ol>

<p>Note: There is no thirteenth change.</p>

